# 📖 Chapter 07 – Technical SEO

---

# 🎯 Chapter Objective

Is chapter me hum Technical SEO ko detail me samjhenge. Aap seekhenge ki Technical SEO kya hota hai, Google website ko kaise crawl aur index karta hai, website ki technical health improve kaise ki jati hai aur kaun-kaun se technical factors ranking ko affect karte hain.

---

# 7.1 What is Technical SEO?

**Technical SEO** website ke backend aur technical configuration ko optimize karne ki process hai jisse search engines website ko easily crawl, index aur understand kar sake.

Simple Words:

> **Technical SEO = Website ko technically Google-friendly banana.**

Agar website technically optimized nahi hai to Google content ko properly read nahi kar paayega.

---

# 7.2 Why Technical SEO is Important?

Ek technically optimized website:

* Fast Crawl Hoti Hai
* Fast Index Hoti Hai
* Better Ranking Paati Hai
* Better User Experience Deti Hai
* Mobile Friendly Hoti Hai
* Secure Hoti Hai

---

# 7.3 Technical SEO Components

Technical SEO me mainly ye components aate hain:

* Crawling
* Indexing
* XML Sitemap
* Robots.txt
* HTTPS
* Website Speed
* Mobile Friendliness
* Canonical URL
* Structured Data
* Core Web Vitals
* 404 Errors
* Redirects

---

# 7.4 Crawling

Google ka crawler (Googlebot) website ke pages ko visit karta hai.

Process:

```text
Googlebot

↓

Homepage

↓

Internal Links

↓

Other Pages

↓

Content Read
```

Agar pages properly linked nahi honge to Google unhe crawl nahi kar paayega.

---

# 7.5 Indexing

Crawling ke baad Google page ko apni database me save karta hai.

Is process ko **Indexing** kehte hain.

Agar page index nahi hua hai to woh Google Search Results me nahi dikhega.

---

# 7.6 XML Sitemap

**XML Sitemap** website ke important pages ki list hoti hai.

Example:

```text
example.com/sitemap.xml
```

Benefits:

* Faster Crawling
* Faster Indexing
* Easy Page Discovery

Har website me sitemap hona chahiye.

---

# 7.7 Robots.txt

Robots.txt Google ko batata hai ki website ke kaunse pages crawl karne hain aur kaunse nahi.

Example:

```text
User-agent: *

Disallow: /admin/

Allow: /

Sitemap: https://example.com/sitemap.xml
```

Use carefully.

Galat configuration se important pages Google se hide ho sakte hain.

---

# 7.8 HTTPS (SSL Certificate)

HTTPS secure website ko represent karta hai.

Example:

✅

```text
https://example.com
```

❌

```text
http://example.com
```

Benefits:

* Better Security
* User Trust
* Google Ranking Signal

---

# 7.9 Mobile Friendliness

Google Mobile-First Indexing use karta hai.

Iska matlab:

Google website ka mobile version pehle check karta hai.

Checklist:

* Responsive Design
* Readable Fonts
* Fast Loading
* Touch Friendly Buttons
* No Horizontal Scrolling

---

# 7.10 Website Speed

Fast websites better ranking aur better user experience deti hain.

Target:

```text
Website Load Time < 2 Seconds
```

Improve Speed:

* Compress Images
* WebP Images
* Browser Caching
* Lazy Loading
* Minify CSS
* Minify JavaScript
* CDN

---

# 7.11 Core Web Vitals

Google User Experience measure karne ke liye Core Web Vitals use karta hai.

### 1. Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)

Page ka main content kitni jaldi load hota hai.

Target:

```text
Less than 2.5 Seconds
```

---

### 2. Interaction to Next Paint (INP)

User interaction kitni quickly respond karti hai.

Target:

```text
Less than 200 ms
```

---

### 3. Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)

Page load hone ke baad layout kitna stable rehta hai.

Target:

```text
Less than 0.1
```

---

# 7.12 Canonical URL

Kabhi-kabhi same content multiple URLs par available hota hai.

Canonical URL Google ko batata hai ki original page kaunsa hai.

Benefits:

* Duplicate Content Avoid
* Better SEO

---

# 7.13 Structured Data (Schema Markup)

Schema Markup Google ko page ka context samajhne me help karta hai.

Examples:

* Product Schema
* Article Schema
* Organization Schema
* FAQ Schema
* Local Business Schema

Benefits:

* Rich Results
* Better Visibility
* Higher CTR

---

# 7.14 404 Error

404 Error tab aata hai jab page exist nahi karta.

Example:

```text
example.com/old-page
```

↓

404 Not Found

Solution:

* 301 Redirect
* Broken Links Fix
* Custom 404 Page

---

# 7.15 301 Redirect

Permanent Redirect.

Old URL

↓

New URL

SEO Value Preserve Hoti Hai.

Example:

```text
old-page

↓

new-page
```

---

# 7.16 Broken Links

Broken Links user experience aur SEO dono ko negatively affect karte hain.

Regularly check karo:

* Internal Links
* External Links
* Images
* Downloads

---

# 7.17 Duplicate Content

Same content multiple pages par nahi hona chahiye.

Problems:

* Ranking Issues
* Indexing Confusion
* Lower Authority

Solution:

* Unique Content
* Canonical Tags

